Catholic normies fundamentally misunderstand Tolkien because they try to prove he's good by pointing at "dat morality" when what matters more is 1000s of hours of Indo-European philology, etymology, European folklore and mythology filtered into a single narrative through one mind

Most "fiction" writers just make cool stuff up but in Tolkien you can trace individual words, concepts, deities, etc. to reality and actual religion. He's not trying to do "literature", if anything it's closer to Lovecraft trying to describe his nocturnal nightmare, a travelogue.

I've linked an essay by a friend before on how e.g. the ring is meant to be an artificial chakra and it all fits with "Hinduism", but you can also link races from the universe with those Nangian 16th century Swedish histories of troll communities, nothing is absolutely subjective

Due to the nebulous "fiction" label people think about Tolkien's stuff like Harry Potter, but if you ask Julius Evola he will tell you that it's best to compare it to Nietzsche. Zarathustra walking down into town to see the acrobat and the jester, dining with his companions, etc.
